      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study must demonstrate discretization error below 5% for hemolysis index QoI using at least three systematically refined meshes with GCI reported.",
      "rationale": "A two-mesh comparison was performed (coarse 4.2M cells, fine 8.6M cells). The hemolysis index differed by 11.3% between meshes. No Richardson extrapolation or GCI calculation was completed. The assessment team judged the difference acceptable given overall model performance, but the formal convergence criterion was not met."
