    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the CFD model provides sufficient evidence to support the regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device. Six of seven assessed factors meet or exceed required levels. The discretization error factor achieved level 1 against a required level of 2; however, the team judged the 11.3% mesh-to-mesh variation to be within engineering expectations for rotodynamic pump flows and accepted the assessment on that basis. Overall assurance level is declared High based on the breadth of validation evidence and the low-to-medium model influence classification.",
